@startuml route_warning_to_hmi_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Route Warning To HMI Signal Flow\n(Input_Console / NAV -> ADAS -> CGW -> IVI / CLU / AMP)

actor "Driver\n(Input Console)" as Driver #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nContext > Inject / Route" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "NAV\nroute context producer" as NAV #E8F7E8
participant "ADAS\nalert decision owner" as ADAS #FCE8FF
participant "CGW\nwarning gateway / fail-safe" as CGW #FFF4CC
participant "IVI\nrender / popup / audio focus" as IVI #E8F0FE
participant "CLU\ncluster warning output" as CLU #E8F0FE
participant "AMP\nducking / audio output" as AMP #FFE6E6

== Route Context Injection ==

Driver -> Panel : Set ROAD ZONE / NAV DIR\nZONE DIST / SPD LIMIT
activate Panel
Panel -> Panel : Write Inject::roadZone\nInject::navDirection
Panel -> Panel : Write Inject::zoneDistance\nInject::speedLimit
deactivate Panel

== NAV Context Publish ==

activate NAV
Panel -> NAV : Inject::* route context
NAV -> NAV : calcBaseZoneContext()\ncalcEffectiveSpeedLimit()
NAV -> ADAS : frmNavModuleStateMsg
NAV -> CGW : frmNavigationRouteMsg
NAV -> IVI : frmNavigationRouteMsg
note right of NAV
Representative outputs
- frmNavModuleStateMsg
- frmNavigationRouteMsg
- route class / guide / distance / speed limit
end note
deactivate NAV

== ADAS Decision ==

activate ADAS
NAV -> ADAS : frmNavModuleStateMsg
ADAS -> ADAS : baseZoneContext / speedLimitNorm
ADAS -> ADAS : selectedAlertDecisionLevel / Type
ADAS -> CGW : CoreState::selectedAlertDecisionLevel
ADAS -> CGW : CoreState::selectedAlertDecisionType
note right of ADAS
Representative logic
- road/speed warning selection
- zone-adjusted warning priority
- direct write to decision seams
end note
deactivate ADAS

== CGW Effective Gate ==

activate CGW
NAV -> CGW : frmNavigationRouteMsg
ADAS -> CGW : decision seams
CGW -> CGW : apply timeout / boundary / fail-safe gate
CGW -> IVI : CoreState::selectedAlertEffectiveLevel / Type
CGW -> CLU : CoreState::selectedAlertEffectiveLevel / Type
CGW -> AMP : CoreState::selectedAlertEffectiveLevel via IVI audio focus path
note right of CGW
Effective outputs
- selectedAlertEffectiveLevel
- selectedAlertEffectiveType
- selectedAlertGateReason
end note
deactivate CGW

== HMI Rendering ==

activate IVI
CGW -> IVI : effective alert seams
IVI -> IVI : deriveWarningTextCode()
IVI -> IVI : derive roadZoneColorCode / renderMode
IVI -> CLU : frmClusterWarningMsg
IVI -> CLU : frmClusterNotifMsg
IVI -> CLU : frmHmiPopupStateMsg
IVI -> AMP : frmAudioFocusMsg
IVI -> AMP : frmMediaStateMsg
note right of IVI
Visible/render seams
- UiRender::warningBeepState
- UiRender::roadZoneColorCode
- Cluster::warningTextCode
end note
deactivate IVI

activate CLU
IVI -> CLU : cluster warning / notif / popup
CLU -> Panel : warning text / notif readback
deactivate CLU

activate AMP
IVI -> AMP : audio focus / media state
AMP -> AMP : ducking / focus owner
deactivate AMP

Driver <- Panel : Route warning is visible in cluster / popup\nand audible through audio ducking

note over Driver, AMP
Representative runtime chain
1. Input_Console injects route context
2. NAV publishes route/state messages
3. ADAS decides warning level/type
4. CGW gates decision into effective alert
5. IVI / CLU / AMP render text, popup, and audio
end note

@enduml
